    <h3>Adding Responsiveness via JS</h3><p>CSS media queries can help us restyle our extension in response to various browser and device sizes. However, CSS will only get us so far. What if we want to make incremental changes to our visualization on resize, instead of re-rendering the whole thing from scratch with our paint function? That’s where our resize function comes into play.</br></br></p><p>Recall our extension lifecycle from before. There are two types of events that trigger rendering: data or properties changing, and the chart container changing size.</p></div><div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6 body-right"><div class="graph" id="resize-extension"><img src="./imgs/resize-extension.png" alt="" class="img-responsive resize-extension"></img></div></div></div></div><div id="section-3"class="section resize-editor"><div class="row">
